      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tough race to start the day. EJECT (4) handy stayer who comes here deep into the prep and due for a change of luck. Motored late from back in the field with a sound fourth over 2100m at this track. Gets the right tempo today and ready to break through. DESCENDING MIST (1) just under a month between runs when back in trip for a plugging ninth over 1600m here. Proven at this distance range and can bounce back quickly. GIDDY GAN'S JOY (3) comes down from the Gold Coast after closing strongly when third over 1900m at the Gold Coast Poly. Will find this a little easier and not to be underestimated. BILL PEYTO (5) doesn't win out of turn but has a good record over this track and trip. Slashing run from near last on the turn with a game second over 1850m at Mudgee. Well drawn and stays in the mix.",
